{{Infobox person | name = Awele Maduemezia | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Awele | birth_date = 8August. 1934 | birth_place = [[Bukuru,Jos,Plateau State]], [[Nigeria]] | othername = Augustine | nationality = Nigerian | citizenship = Nigerian | occupation ={{flatlist| * educator *mathematician *researcher}} }}
'''Awele Maduemezia''' is a [[Nigerian]] Professor of [[Physics]] . He was born in 1934. He was former [[Vice-Chancellor|Vice Chancellor]] of [[Ambrose Alli University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailyindependentnig.com/2015/04/nigerian-varsities-growing-without-development-maduemezia/|title=Nigerian varsities growing without development –Maduemezia|work=Daily Independent|accessdate=June 10, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150711174634/http://dailyindependentnig.com/2015/04/nigerian-varsities-growing-without-development-maduemezia/|archive-date=2015-07-11|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> . He also served as president of the [[Nigerian Association of Mathematical Physics]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2011/06/121-entries-25-nominations-for-2011-nigeria-prize-for-literature-science/|title=121 entries, 25 nominations for 2011 Nigeria Prize for Literature, Science|work=Vanguard News|accessdate=June 10, 2015}}</ref>
In 1995, he was elected as President of the [[Nigerian Academy of Science]] to succeed Professor [[Anthony Afolabi Adegbola]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nas.org.ng/fellowship/members-of-council/ |title=Members of Council |work=Nigerian Academy of Science |accessdate=June 7, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707061854/http://www.nas.org.ng/fellowship/members-of-council/ |archivedate=July 7, 2015 |df= }}</ref> He died on 20 February 2018.
