In mathematics, the '''Baily–Borel compactification''' is a [[compactification (mathematics)|compactification]] of a quotient of a [[Hermitian symmetric space]] by an [[arithmetic group]], introduced by  {{harvs|txt=yes|first1=Walter L.|last1= Baily|author1-link=Walter Lewis Baily, Jr.|first2=  Armand|last2= Borel|year1=1964|year2=1966|author2-link=Armand Borel}}.

==Example==
*If ''C'' is the quotient of the upper half plane by a [[congruence subgroup]] of SL<sub>2</sub>('''Z'''), then the Baily–Borel compactification of ''C'' is formed by adding a finite number of cusps to it.

