==Modern Greek mathematicians== *[[Leonidas Alaoglu]] (1914–1981) - Known for ''Banach- Alaoglu theorem''.<ref>{{cite book|title=Integral and Functional Analysis|first=Jie|last=Xiao|publisher=Nova Publishers|page=1996|year=2008}}</ref> *[[Charalambos D. Aliprantis]] (1946–2009) - Founder and Editor-in-Chief of the journals Economic Theory as well as Annals of Finance.<ref>{{cite web|title=Charalambos D. Aliprantis passed away|url=https://www.springer.com/economics?SGWID=0-165-2-699309-0}}</ref> *[[Roger Apéry]] (1916–1994) - Professor of mathematics and mechanics at the [[University of Caen Lower Normandy|University of Caen]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Number Theory and Related Fields: In Memory of Alf van der Poorten|author1=Jonathan Borwein|author2=Igor Shparlinski|author3=Wadim Zudilin|page=5|year=2013|publisher=Springer}}</ref> *[[Tom M. Apostol]] (1923-2016) - Professor of mathematics in [[California Institute of Technology]],<ref>{{cite book|title=The Mechanical Universe: Mechanics and Heat, Advanced Edition|author1= Richard P. Olenick|author2=Tom M. Apostol|page=588|publisher=Cambridge University Press}}</ref> he has authored a number of books about mathematics. *[[Dimitri Bertsekas]] (born 1942) - Member of the National Academy of Engineering professor with the Department of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science. Author of fifteen books and research monographs, and coauthor of an introductory probability textbook<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.edx.org/course/mitx/mitx-6-041x-introduction-probability-1296#.U0fEAfmSwrU |title=Introduction to Probability - The Science of Uncertainty |publisher=edX}}</ref> *[[Giovanni Carandino]] (1784–1834) *[[Constantin Carathéodory]] (1873–1950) - Mathematician who pioneered the Axiomatic Formulation of Thermodynamics.<ref>Mathematical Reviews - Volume 2003 - Page 4687, year = 2003</ref> *[[Demetrios Christodoulou]] (born 1951) - Mathematician-physicist who has contributed in the field of general relativity.<ref>''MacArthur