om/biography/Metropolis.html |title=Metropolis, Nicholas Constantine (1915-1999) - from Eric Weisstein's World of Scientific Biography |publisher=Scienceworld.wolfram.com |date=1952-03-15}}</ref> *[[Yiannis N. Moschovakis]] (1938) - Writer, also worked as theorist in [[University of California, Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Descriptive Set Theory|year=1987|page=vii|first=Y.N.|last=Moschovakis}}</ref> *[[Christos Papakyriakopoulos]] (1914–1976) - Often called ''Papa'', he specialized in [[geometric topology]].<ref>{{cite book|title=The History of Science and Technology: 1900-1970|page=704|first=Edgardo|last=Macorini|year=1988}}</ref> *[[Athanasios Papoulis]] (1921–2002) - Contributed a number of theories, such as ''Papoulis–Gerchberg algorithm'',<ref>R. W. Gerchberg, Super-resolution through error energy reduction. Opt. Acta 21, 709-720 (1974)</ref> ''A eloquent proof'',<ref>{{cite book|title=Handbook of Fourier Analysis & Its Applications|page=223|year=2008|first=Robert J|last=Marks}}</ref> among others. *[[Themistocles M. Rassias]] (born 1951) - Professor at the [[National Technical University of Athens]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Functional Equations, Inequalities and Applications|page=7|first=T.M.|last=Rassias|publisher=Springer|year=2003}}</ref> *[[Raphaël Salem]] (1898-1963) - Was a Greek mathematician after whom are named the [[Salem number]]s and whose widow founded the [[Salem Prize]]. *[[Cyparissos Stephanos]] (1857–1917) - Notable contributor of [[desmic system]]s.<ref>{{cite book|title=Applied Geometry and Discrete Mathematics: The Victor Klee Festschrift|publisher=American Mathematical Soc.|author1=Peter Gritzmann|author2=Bernd Sturmfels|author3=Victor Klee|page=415}}</ref> *[[Katia Sycara]] - Professor in the Carnegie Mellon School of Computer Science's Robotics Institute and the director of the Laboratory for Agents technology and Semantic web technologies.<ref>{{cite book|title=Terrorism Informatics: Knowledge Management and Data Mining for Homeland Security|page=39|author1=Hsinchun Chen|author2=Edna Reid|author3=Joshua Sinai|author4=Andrew Silke|author5=Boaz Ganor|year=2008|publisher=Springer|isbn=9780387716138}}</ref> *[[Nicholas Varopoulos]] (born 1940) - Notable for his analysis on Lie groups.<ref>{{cite book |title= Random Walks and Discrete Potential Theory |page=356 |author1= M. Picardello |author2=W. Woess |date= 1999 |publisher= Cambridge University Press}}</ref> *[[Stathis Zachos]] (born 1947) - Published a number of writings on [[computer science]]. *[[Mihail Zervos]] - Working in Department of Mathematics, [[London School of Economics]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Modern Trends in Controlled Stochastic Processes|page=161|publisher=Luniver Press|first=Alexey B.|last=Piunovskiy|year=2010|isbn=9781905986309}}</ref>
